org.eng.util

Class MutatingShuffleIterable<INPUT,OUTPUT>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.eng.util.AbstractReferenceShuffleIterable<OUTPUT,ISizedShuffleIterable<OUTPUT>>
      • org.eng.util.MutatingShuffleIterable<INPUT,OUTPUT>
  • Type Parameters:
    INPUT - type of item iterated over to produce OUTPUT items.
    OUTPUT - type of item produced from an INPUT item.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Iterable<OUTPUT>, IItemReferenceIterable<OUTPUT>, IShuffleIterable<OUTPUT>, ISizedIterable<OUTPUT>, ISizedShuffleIterable<OUTPUT>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    DataWindowLabelingShuffleIterable, FixedDurationSoundRecordingShuffleIterable, LabeledWindowShuffleIterable, LabeledWindowToDataWindowShuffleIterable, SegmentingSoundRecordingShuffleIterable, TransformingSizedShuffleIterable

    public class MutatingShuffleIterable<INPUT,OUTPUT>
extends AbstractReferenceShuffleIterable<OUTPUT,ISizedShuffleIterable<OUTPUT>>
implements ISizedShuffleIterable<OUTPUT>
    Provides mutation of items in an IShuffleIterable by extending the super class and forcing the use of IShuffleIterable in the constructor. Mutation is defined with an IShuffleMutator instance that indicates whether or not the the mutator produces more than 1 output for any of its inputs. Mutation is applied in the dereference(String) implementation, but in addition, the determine a full set of shufflable references, the constructor will iterate and mutate all items to determine a unique reference for each OUTPUT.
    Author:
    dawood

      • MutatingShuffleIterable

        public MutatingShuffleIterable(IShuffleIterable<INPUT> iterable,
                               IShuffleMutator<INPUT,OUTPUT> mutator)
        Create the instance to mutate the given iterable of INPUT to OUTPUT. If the given mutator is NOT unary, this will iterator and mutate all instances to determine a unique reference for each mutated OUTPUT.
        Parameters:
        iterable - the INPUT data to transform to 0 or more OUTPUT values.
        mutator - a stateless function to convert an INPUT to a list of OUTPUT.
